post_text: All EHS athletes are encouraged to participate in our fall practice days from September 7-October 31. These days are approved by IHSA and replace the summer camp days that were not allowed this year. These practices will not affect an athletes position on a team. Please take note of the attached schedule and come ready to practice. All student athletes must have a current sports physical on file and will need to wear a mask if practicing inside and when they are not social distancing while practicing outside. If you are currently a golfer or cross country runner, those sports are your priority. Please contact Mr. Collins with any questions scollins@earlville9.org

post_text: Due to State guidelines limiting indoor gatherings to under 50 people, and the inability to maintain social distancing, we regret to announce that Prom, scheduled for August 1, 2020 is cancelled. Reimbursement for tickets is available in the office. Graduation will continue to occur on July 31, 2020 as we will have an outdoor ceremony on the soccer field. Eighth grade and high school will graduate at different times with eighth grade graduation occurring at 4:00 p.m. and high school beginning at 6:00 p.m. Graduates will be seated six feet apart. Each graduate will have four chairs for their family members set up in groups of two, six feet apart. Chairs will be disinfected between ceremonies. Masks are required where proper social distancing cannot be maintained. Graduates will be required to wear masks. Everyone is invited to this event and any member beyond the four reserved chairs set up per family should plan to bring a lawn chair, blanket etc. We will monitor the weather as we approach the event and notify you of accommodations to the event via the live feed and Facebook.

Eighth grade and high school will graduate at different times with eighth grade graduation occurring at 4:00 p.m. and high school beginning at 6:00 p.m. Graduates will be seated six feet apart. Each graduate will have four chairs for their family members set up in groups of two, six feet apart. Chairs will be disinfected between ceremonies. Masks are required where proper social distancing cannot be maintained. Graduates will be required to wear masks. Everyone is invited to this event and any member beyond the four reserved chairs set up per family should plan to bring a lawn chair, blanket etc. We will monitor the weather as we approach the event and notify you of accommodations to the event via the live feed and Facebook.

post_text:
Dear Earlville Familes,
It is with a very heavy heart that I inform you that the governor has ordered that in person instruction remain suspended for the rest of the 19-20 academic year. We will continue with our e-learning plan for the remainder of the academic year. I will be in touch early next week detailing our plans for events that are cancelled as a result of this closure including graduation, awards nights, and prom..We will also communicate a plan for students to pick up materials. Please look for these details to be posted on Tuesday, April 21. Thank you again for the opportunity to work for the greatest students in the world. If you have any questions or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact me at 815-993-0973.

post_text: As you are likely aware, Governor Pritzker has ordered that schools remain closed through April 30. We would like to commend you on the work your students are doing remotely. Keep up the great work. I want to communicate what the coming weeks will look like. First, there will be no remote learning on April 10 and April 13 as school was not originally scheduled on those days. Further, remote learning will now occur every Tuesday through Friday, as each Monday will be reserved as teacher planning days. That means students will not engage in remote learning on April 6, 10, 13, 20, or 27. All other days Tuesday-Friday will continue to be remote learning days. Please continue to follow the e-learning plan. In closing, it is a real honor to work for the greatest students in the world. Please keep up the great work.

Earlville Fire Protection District
March 31 at 8:11 PM ¬∑

While we are all practicing social distancing, the department would like to take this opportunity to make a child's day, young or old (age doesn't matter as we're all children at heart). In following with other area departments, we would like to provide the opportunity to do a birthday drive by for those that can't celebrate right now. We will stop in front of the celebrants house at a designated time of your choice, flash our lights and make a little noise with our sirens to celebrate their birthday. To continue practicing safe social distancing we ask that you remain on your front porch or near your front door. To make arrangements, please message our page administrator or email earlvilleamb@gmail.com and we will gladly provide a little happiness!

Dear Parents,
As a reminder Monday will be an E-Learning Day, please follow the guidelines in the letter. If any student needs to pick up materials please stop by the office on Monday between 8:30 -10:30am and we will get your materials. Also, as a reminder if you do not have internet at home please let your child‚Äôs teacher know, as we are collecting a list so we can address those.
We will be offering a drive through food service during this week. Monday, breakfast will be offered from 7:30-8:30. Breakfast pick up will happen at the south west cafeteria door, directly across from the raider head entrance. Each student‚Äôs normal fee rate applies. On Monday, cafeteria staff will meet to plan meals for the rest of the week. We will serve at least one meal daily. In order to get breakfast on Monday, simply drive or walk up to the cafeteria door, and staff will assist you. Thank you again for being so understanding and supportive!

post_text: At 3:30 today, the Governor directed all schools to be closed from March 17-March 30th. He left open the possibility that the closure will extend beyond that date. Given this directive, we will not be in session beginning immediately through March 30th. The next scheduled attendance day is Tuesday, March 31 however the closure could extend beyond that date. We will obviously communicate any extension. March 16 will be the first e-learning day and each subsequent non attendance day will be considered an e-learning day with the exception of Spring Break (March 23-27). Please follow the elearning directions sent home and posted to social media today. . All athletic events during the closure are cancelled and coaches should not have practice. Any community events scheduled to occur at school should also be cancelled including 3-4 basketball, adult volleyball, club volleyball. Students will not attend IVVC on Monday.

post_text:
Regarding the JH Spelling Bee...
The Jr. 10 continues to actively monitor reports on COVID-19 and follow guidance from the Illinois Department of Public Health and local health departments.

The Jr. 10 has decided to postpone the Jr. 10 Spelling Bee at Serena High School scheduled for March 17th. We are evaluating each Conference event as the situation continues to evolve.

All decisions are being made with the safety and well being of our students in mind, and we are being as responsive as possible with the information we are gathering.
